        <headline>Heat Advisory issued July 23 at 2:30AM EDT until July 24 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Heat index values 98 to 102 this afternoon and early
evening, falling into the low to mid 70s tonight.  Heat index
values 100 to 105 expected Thursday afternoon with isolated values
to 108 possible.

* WHERE...Portions of northern Indiana and southwest Michigan.

* WHEN...From 2 PM EDT /1 PM CDT/ this afternoon to 8 PM EDT /7 PM
CDT/ Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures and high humidity may cause heat
illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
